{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/well-built-style/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Desk Diver","author":"Andrew Artajos"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"b2e7f424-d2c8-5c13-9e96-9653c05a423b","excerpt":"Three key points to take in here: 1. Physique Men’s style is really about the body. A muscular body is the base of the clothes you wear. You don’t have to be…","html":"<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Style is not just about WHAT your wear but HOW you wear it. Seth Rogen here wearing a plain t-shirt, dark denim jeans. Items I fully endorse. But look at the fit and the lack of physique. Not helping him at all.<br><br>Credit: <a href=\"https://t.co/JD5HgB9eCh\">https://t.co/JD5HgB9eCh</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/03vRaEWCJt\">pic.twitter.com/03vRaEWCJt</a></p>&mdash; WellBuiltStyle (@WellBuiltStyle) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/WellBuiltStyle/status/1157095698388570112?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">August 2, 2019</a></blockquote> <script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 95.10961214165262%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"classic style\"\n        title=\"classic style\"\n        src=\"/static/15615d6732e404ea9cbb7717b521c341/799d3/wellbuiltstyle.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/15615d6732e404ea9cbb7717b521c341/00d96/wellbuiltstyle.png 148w,\n/static/15615d6732e404ea9cbb7717b521c341/0b23c/wellbuiltstyle.png 295w,\n/static/15615d6732e404ea9cbb7717b521c341/799d3/wellbuiltstyle.png 590w,\n/static/15615d6732e404ea9cbb7717b521c341/914f1/wellbuiltstyle.png 593w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Three key points to take in here:</h2>\n<h3>1. Physique</h3>\n<p>Men’s style is really about the body. A muscular body is the base of the clothes you wear. You don’t have to be really jacked like a super hero. You got to take care of the body and do the work in the gym. Build a strong and imposing physique — without it everything would look sloppy.</p>\n<h3>2. Plain</h3>\n<p>Stick to solid colours. No branding.</p>\n<h3>3. Fit</h3>\n<p>It has to fit perfectly. Big mistake made by muscular men is picking clothes that are way too tight. On the other end of the spectrum, regular joes tend to pick clothes that are way too big — making it look sloppy.</p>\n<p><em>for my 2 cents I also recommend having regular haircuts. I have a reminder in my calendar every month to get a haircut. It helps me look sharp.</em></p>\n<p>For more details follow:\n<a href=\"https://twitter.com/WellBuiltStyle/status/1157095698388570112?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@WellBuiltStyle</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Style doesn't have to be complicated","date":"October 20, 2019","description":"Stay fit. Look sharp."}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/well-built-style/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/3-tips-for-better-sex/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"3 Tips for better sex"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/reading-is-fundamental/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Reading is fundamental"}}}}}